Description: Scraggly tree 4 metres tall. Bark rough, coarsely tessellated, grey. Leaves dull, slightly rough, light green. Dominant on gravely red sand, with Corymbia opaca nearby. PERTH

Location: Kelly's Knob, Kununurra township, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 4 m tall. Bark smooth, white and pinkish-cream. Leaves dull, green. Growing in between rocks on rocky hill with Corymbia cliftoniana? and C. drysdalensis. CANB, PERTH photo

Location: South of Yeo Lake, Great Victoria Desert, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 6m tall. Bark rough for 203m, grey brown, then smooth, white. Leaves dull, blue green at first, becoming glossy, green. In red sand with Eucalyptus lucasii. Photos AD

Description: Tree 10 m tall. Bark smooth, white. Leaves dull, light green. Growing with Corymbia ferruginea, C. polycarpa, Eucalyptus camaldulensis var. obtusa and E. patellaris. Photo AD

Description: Whipstick mallee 5 m tall. Bark smooth, tan and grey over pale orange. Leaves glossy, dark green. Growing in very small waterway with Corymbia maculata, Eucalyptus moluccana and E. fibrosa. Photos AD

Location: south of Kew on Pacific HW, NSW
Description: Tree 30m tall. Bark rough, tessellated, dark grey for about 1m then smooth white. Leaves discolourous, glossy, green. Growing beside creek with E. pilularis and E. microcorys. Photo AD

Location: south of Kew on Pacific HW, NSW
Description: Tree 30m tall. Bark rough, tessellated, dark grey for about 1m then smooth white. Leaves discolourous, glossy, green. Growing beside creek with E. pilularis and E. microcorys. Photo AD

Description: Scraggly multi-stemmed tree 4 metres tall. Bark rough and tessellated, brown. Leaves discolorous, glossy, dark green. Growing on gravely sand with Eucalyptus uvida. Photo  AD

Location: Blue Mountains National Park, near Glenbrook, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 8 m tall. Bark rough to small branches, finely fissured, grey. Leaves dull, blue-green. Growing on edge of ridge with A. costata, E. sparsifolia, C. gummifera and Syncarpia. AD, CANB Photo

Location: Blue Mountains National Park, near Glenbrook, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 14 metres tall. Bark smooth, grey and pink over orange. Leaves discolorous, glossy and green above. Growing with Corymbia gummifera, C. eximia, Eucalyptus racemosa and Syncarpia. AD, CANB

Location: Blue Mountains National Park, near Glenbrook, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 14 metres tall. Bark smooth, grey and pink over orange. Leaves discolorous, glossy and green above. Growing with Corymbia gummifera, C. eximia, Eucalyptus racemosa and Syncarpia. AD, CANB

Location: Helidon Hills, north-east of Helidon, Queensland.
Description: Tree 15 m tall. Bark smooth, grey over light grey. Leaves discolorous, glossy, green above. Growing with Corymbia variegata, C. ?intermedia and Eucalyptus taurina. AD Photo

Location: Near Narooma, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 18 metres tall. Bark smooth, blotched grey over cream. Leaves glossy, green. Growing on hillside in a nearly pure stand, with a few Eucalyptus botryoides. AD

Location: Near Narooma, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 18 metres tall. Bark smooth, blotched grey over cream. Leaves glossy, green. Growing on hillside in a nearly pure stand, with a few Eucalyptus botryoides. AD

Description: Multi-stemmed tree 6 metres tall. Bark rough, tessellated, soft, grey-brown. Leaves slightly discolorous, dull, pale green. Growing in red sand with mulga scrub. AD, CANB Photos

Location: North of St George on the Carnarvon Highway, Queensland.
Description: Tree 10 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, finely fissured, hard, grey-brown. Leaves discolorous, dull and green above. Growing on sandy plain with Corymbia tessellaris, Eucalyptus melanophloia subsp. melanophloia and E. populnea. AD

Location: Daly Waters area on the Stuart Highway, NT.
Description: Tree 10 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, powdery white and pale pink. Leaves slightly glossy, green. Growing in small creek with Corymbia polycarpa and Eucalyptus bigalerita. AD, CANB

Description: Mallee 3 metres tall. Bark rough for < 1 metre. Leaves very slightly glossy, green. On yellow sandplain. Nearby is Eucalyptus subangusta subsp. subangusta, E. sp. Kalbarri, E eudesmioides and E. oldfieldii. PERTH + seeds

Location: Frith Rd, north-east of Clarendon, South Australia.
Description: Poor-formed tree to 4 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, dull, pale grey to cream. Common here on broad ridge in low dense woodland with Eucalyptus obliqua. AD + seeds

Location: Between Walpole and Mt Frankland, N of Walpole, Western Australia.
Description: Tree to 25 metres tall. Bark rough throughout, stringy-fibrous, grey-brown over red-brown. Leaves strongly discolorous, glossy and dark green above. Growing on moderate slope in tall forest, relatively uncommon, with Corymbia calophylla and Eucalyptus diversicolor. AD, PERTH

Location: Boulder Hill, S of Manypeaks, Western Australia.
Description: Sprawling dense 'mallee' to 2 m tall. Leaves more or less dull, light green to dark green. Old dead flowers red to orange. About 50+ clumps on south facing slope in white peaty sand between granite boulders with some Eucalyptus marginata subsp. marginata. Corymbia calophylla nearby but not mixed in stand. PERTH + seed + photos

Location: Boulder Hill, S of Manypeaks, Western Australia.

Location: Track from Gibb River Road to new Mount Elizabeth Homestead, WA
Description: Tree 6m tall. Bark rough throughout, thick, somewhat stringy, orange-tan. Leaves slightly discolourous, dull, blue-green. On rocky rise with C. collina, C. drysdalensis and C. ferruginea ssp. stypophylla. PERTH

Location: Yunta Creek, ca. 2 km S of Yunta on Spring Dam road, South Australia.
Description: Tree to 20 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey and white. Leaves dull, blue-green. Branchlets not pruinose.  Dominant tree in major sandy creek bed. AD, CANB, MEL Seeds

Location: Flinders Highway, Queensland.
Description: Tree to 15 metres tall. Bark rough to 2 to 4.5 metres up, flaky-papery; smooth and white above. Branchlets pruinose.  On pale sandy soil on flat topography in woodland with Corymbia setosa subsp. pedicellaris, C. erythrophloia and Eucalyptus similis. AD

Location: Gum Flat, just east of Minlaton on Stansbury road, Yorke Peninsula, South Australia.
Description: Tree to 15 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey-tan over pale pink, cream and slightly butter yellow-cream. Leaves dull, blue-green. Growing in broad depression in open woodland on brown loam over limestone with Casuarina obesa?, Eucalyptus porosa and Melaleuca. AD

Location: Gum Flat, just east of Minlaton on Stansbury road, Yorke Peninsula, South Australia.
Description: Tree to 15 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, pale grey-tan over pale pink, cream and slightly butter yellow-cream. Leaves dull, blue-green. Growing in broad depression in open woodland on brown loam over limestone with Casuarina obesa?, Eucalyptus porosa and Melaleuca. AD

Location: Jerrawangala Lookout, Jerrawangala National Park, New South Wales.
Description: Tree to 35 metres tall. Bark rough to 100 to 120 mm diameter, moderately fissured, grey-brown. Leaves discolorous, glossy and mid-green above. Below and on sandstone cliff/escarpment in +/- pure forest stand. AD Photos + seeds

Location: Nicholls Rd, Bebo State Forest, New South Wales.
Description: Scraggly mallee to 6 metres tall. Bark rough over most of stems, moderately coarsely fissured, grey. Leaves dull, blue-green. Small stand on top of sandstone rise with Corymbia trachyphloia subsp. amphistomatica, and with Eucalyptus dealbata and E. melanophloia subsp. melanophloia nearby. AD Photos + seeds

Location: Near Blyth River on Ramingining to Maningrida road, Northern Territory.
Description: Tree 12 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, + dull, not powdery, pale grey over white and yellow-cream. Leaves + dull, pale green. Dominant tree here, first seen of this species seen comming via Bulman, growing in broad swamp of loam with some Corymbia ptychocarpa subsp. aptycha, C. polycarpa and Eucalyptus tetrodonta. AD, CANB, DNA Photos

Location: Barakula State Forest scientific area, Queensland.
Description: Multi-stemmed erect tree to 7 metres tall. Bark rough to small branches, stringy-fibrous, grey-brown over red-brown. Leaves discolorous, slightly glossy and dark green above. On pale grey-brown sand with Corymbia bloxsomei, Eucalyptus panda and E. fibrosa. AD Seeds

Location: East of Lake Grace towards Newdegate, Western Australia.
Description: Mallee 6 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, dull, pale grey and pinkish over slightly powdery white. Leaves glossy, slightly blue-green. Flowers cream. Growing on broad rise of white sand over laterite with Eucalyptus albida. CANB, PERTH

Location: Wiluna to Granite Peak road, near Camel Well, Western Australia.
Description: Tree 10 metres tall. Bark smooth throughout, light grey over white over yellowish cream. Leaves dull, greyish. Branchlets, buds and fruits glaucous. Growing in a pure stand on plain of deep red sand. CANB, PERTH

Location: Acsent to New England Tableland from Grafton on Gwydir Highway, New South Wales.
Description: Tree 25 m tall. Bark smooth throughout, grey-green over light grey. Leaves very discolorous, glossy and green above. Growing on steep slope in dense wet forest with Eucalyptus campanulata and E. microcorys. AD

Mallee 3m tall. Bark rough, dark grey brown for about 1m then smooth tan. Leaves glossy, green. No parts glaucous. Growing on red sand with E. odontocarpa - gamophylla intergrades and E. pachyphylla. A Photo
